com.apriori.collections

Class TransformingListIterator<I,O>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.apriori.collections.TransformingIterator<I,O>
      • com.apriori.collections.TransformingListIterator<I,O>
  • Type Parameters:
    I - the "input" type; the type of the wrapped iterator
    O - the "output" type; the type of elements in this iterator
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.util.Iterator<O>, java.util.ListIterator<O>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    TransformingListIterator.Bidi, TransformingListIterator.ReadOnly

    public class TransformingListIterator<I,O>
extends TransformingIterator<I,O>
implements java.util.ListIterator<O>
    A list iterator whose elements are the results of applying a function to results from another iterator. This iterator is simply a wrapper.

    Since transformations can only be done in one direction, some operations are not supported. Namely, add(Object) and set(Object) throw UnsupportedOperationException.

    See Also:
    TransformingListIterator.ReadOnly, TransformingListIterator.Bidi
